data.question: Which of the following statements is false for the properties of electromagnetic waves?
data.opt1: Both electric and magnetic field vectors attain the maxima and minima at the same place and the same time.
data.opt2:
The energy in an electromagnetic wave is divided equal between electric and
magnetic vectors.
data.opt3: Both electric and magnetic field vectors are parallel to each other and perpendicular to the direction of Propagation of the wave.
data.opt4: These waves do not require any material medium for propagation.
